hopobject.body: We used to work together fairway physiotherapy With the help of Curiosity's measurements of the Martian air, isotope analysis suggests that Mars actually had a very thick atmosphere some 4 billion years ago. Without the protection of a global magnetic field, however, the planet wasn't able to retain its atmospheric gases from the ravages of the solar wind that stripped it into space. This is one factor that likely impacted the red planet's habitability.
